**Game Analysis**

1. d4 d5: White opens the game with a Queen's Pawn Opening, controlling the center and preparing for future development.
2. Bf4 Na6: White develops the bishop to f4, aiming to control the long diagonal. Black responds with a knight to a6, preparing to fianchetto the other knight on b7.
3. e3 e6: White pushes the pawn to e3, supporting the pawn on d4 and preparing to develop the dark-squared bishop.

7. Bd3 Qc8: White develops the bishop to d3, eyeing the long diagonal. Black moves the queen to c8, connecting the rooks and preparing for further development.
8. e4 b4: White advances the e-pawn in the center, aiming to open up the position. Black counters with b4, attacking the c3 pawn and aiming to create weaknesses.
9. e5 Ne4: White pushes the e-pawn further, gaining space and threatening the knight on e4. Black captures on c3 with the knight, aiming to eliminate a defender of the e4 knight.
10. Nxe4 dxe4: White captures the knight on e4 with the knight. Black captures the pawn on e4, aiming to open up the position and target White's king.
11. Bxe4 bxc3: White sacrifices the bishop to open up the b-file. Black captures the bishop on e4 and then on c3, gaining material advantage.
12. Bxa8 Qxa8: White takes the rook on a8. Black recaptures the bishop on a8, maintaining the material advantage.
13. bxc3 Ba3: White pushes the b-pawn, creating a passed pawn. Black develops the light-squared bishop to a3, attacking the c1 square.
14. Rb1 c5: White moves the rook to b1, aiming to support the pawn on b7. Black advances the c-pawn, aiming to open up lines for the pieces.

**Summary of Strategies Used:**
- White aimed to control the center early in the game and develop the pieces harmoniously.
- Black focused on counterattacking and creating pawn weaknesses to exploit.
- Both sides played energetically, seizing opportunities and tactics throughout the game.

**Winner:** Black, by delivering a checkmate with Qe8#. Black was able to capitalize on the material advantage gained earlier and convert it into a winning position.
